Document: 1
{"content":"Destiny's Child's self-titled debut album was released on February 17, 1998.

Their second studio album, The Writing's on the Wall, was released on July 27, 1999.

The group's third album, Survivor, came out on May 1, 2001.

Their fourth studio album, Destiny Fulfilled, was released on November 15, 2004.

Following this, the group officially disbanded in 2006.

In 2013, Destiny's Child reunited for the Super Bowl XLVII halftime show.

For those interested, the group's discography consists of four studio albums, one holiday album, one remix album, two compilation albums, and four soundtrack albums.

The group's singles include: 'No, No, No', 'Bills, Bills, Bills', 'Say My Name', 'Jumpin', Jumpin', 'Survivor', 'Bootylicious', 'Independent Women Part I', 'Emotion', 'Brown Eyes', 'Lose My Breath', 'Soldier', 'Girl', 'Cater 2 U', 'Stand Up for Love', and more.

The group's other albums include Destiny's Child (their self-titled debut album), The Writing's on the Wall (their second album), Survivor (their third album), Destiny Fulfilled (their fourth album), Number 1's (a compilation album), 8 Days of Christmas (the holiday album), This Is the Remix (the remix album), and Destiny's Child World Tour (a live album).

In 2017, Destiny's Child were inducted into the Vocal Group Hall of Fame.

Some of the group's awards include three Grammy Awards, two American Music Awards, and two Billboard Music Awards.

Fun fact: Destiny's Child was originally named 'Girl's Tyme'.

Source: www.destinyschild.net",
"link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Destiny%27s_Child"}
